comments: Allen (CLE) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
The game is stopped due to a game clock malfunction. After correcting the clock, the game correctly resumes with DAL retaining possession.
Allen (CLE) and Kleber (DAL) briefly engage and disengage with one another in the lane.
Garland (CLE) legally contests Green's (DAL) jump shot, making contact with the ball prior to "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Kleber (DAL) cleanly blocks Garland's (CLE) driving shot attempt and the contact to the body is marginal.
Irving (DAL) overtly hooks his off-arm around Strus' (CLE) left arm and initiates contact that affects Strus' ability to defend the drive.
Doncic (DAL) maintains a legal guarding position as Mitchell (CLE) loses control of the ball.
Allen (CLE) and Kleber (DAL) engage off ball and marginal contact occurs as Allen releases away to disengage.
Allen (CLE) establishes himself in Green's (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) is absorbing the initial contact that occurs with LeVert (CLE) and incidental contact occurs as LeVert attempts to move over the screen.
Green (DAL) gets his hand on the ball to tie up Garland (CLE) before incidental contact occurs between the two players.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Strus (CLE) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes OOB.
Allen (CLE) gets to the height of the ball and makes contact with it during Washington's (DAL) shot attempt at the basket.  Any ensuing contact with Washington's wrist is marginal.
Doncic (DAL) contests the shot attempt and avoids making contact with Strus' (CLE) arms.
